  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large skillet, cook the ground turkey over medium-high heat until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add the roasted vegetables, mashed potatoes, and nutty bread crumbs to the skillet. Stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "If using bacon, sprinkle it on top of the mixture.",
    "Sprinkle the cheddar cheese over the top.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Serve hot."
